    <h1>AMER&#xAD;I&#xAD;CANA FLAIR</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210109/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-09"><time>2021-01-09</time></a>
        - <span>HOME DECOR</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Fans of tra­di­tional in­te­rior de­sign, a style com­monly spot­ted in Amer­i­can homes, must visit the King Koil flag­ship gallery. It car­ries King Koil's sig­na­ture in­di­vid­ual pock­eted spring mat­tresses and so­fas, and shares the space with Ash­ley Fur­ni­ture Home­store, an Amer­i­can brand known for their tra­di­tional and rus­tic farm­house de­signs.</p>
    <p>Shop­pers can en­joy an end-to-end re­tail ex­pe­ri­ence start­ing with a mat­tress that pro­vides you with a life­time of com­fort. King Koil’s chi­ro­prac­tor-tested op­tions, de­signed to pro­mote op­ti­mal spine sup­port while keep­ing mois­ture, bac­te­ria and odours at bay, tick all boxes.</p>
    <p>Com­ple­ment yours with Ash­ley Fur­ni­ture Home­store’s bed frames. High tufted head­boards are quin­tes­sen­tial to the tra­di­tional style, but those look­ing for more prac­ti­cal de­signs can opt for chic wooden frames with pull-out draw­ers.</p>
    <p>The rest of your home can be kit­ted out with fur­ni­ture and home ac­cents of sim­i­lar styles, be it din­ing room ta­bles and benches, of­fice book­cases, or mir­rors for the hall­way.</p>
    <p>Visit the flag­ship King Koil Gallery at</p>
    <p>#01-01, 1 Gent­ing Lane, tel: 6747-0488. For more in­for­ma­tion, visit www.kingkoil.com.sg and www.shop.ash­ley­fur­ni­ture.sg.</p>

